So... stay tuned for my latest bloodworks results! 🙃

(6/6)

It's been almost 3 months since my E dose was increased to 3mg so I should get new bloodworks in a few weeks. I fully expect E to have helped nuke my T even more, and expect E to be much higher than my pre HRT levels simply based on the effects I've experienced.

(5/6)

After that my E dose was increased to 3mg which can be considered a transition dose, and the difference became quite obvious in just a few weeks, especially in the emotional aspect but also in a few physical aspects (though nothing to call home about). 
(4/6)

6 Months MPA + 3 months 1mg E (oral):
T: 47.5 ng/dL
E: 19.5 pg/mL

By this time I had pretty much become a hormonally asexual creature.

I was a little concerned by E staying almost the same, but apparently this was sort of to be expected from such a low dose + MPA.

(3/6)

3 Months MPA only (no E):
T: 218.6 ng/dL
E: 18.6 pg/mL

Yes, MPA lowers both T and E.

After this I decided it was time to start E, and was started on a very low dose.

(2/6)
